text: Malokyzylbayevo () is a rural locality (a village) in Alegazovsky Selsoviet, Mechetlinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 75 as of 2010. There is 1 street. == Geography == It is located 14 km from Bolsheustyikinskoye, 2 km from Alegazovo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mechetlinsky District
title: Malokyzylbayevo
